<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="337" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[675,1211,551,866]" pageId="12" pageNumber="337">
DISTRIBUTION. — This arboreal species is very common in ER IV and also quite frequently encountered in ER II, III and V. The confirmed northern limit of its range is Aledjo but it might also occur in the region of the 
<collectingRegion box="[1157,1206,631,655]" country="Togo" name="Kara" pageId="12" pageNumber="337">Kara</collectingRegion>
, especially in forests of Djamdè and Sarakawa. 
<bibRefCitation author="STERNFELD L." pageId="12" pageNumber="337" refId="ref29026" refString="STERNFELD L. 1909. - Die Schlangen Togos, in Die Fauna der deutschen Kolonien 1 (1): iv + 29 p., map." type="book" year="1909">Sternfeld (1909: 24)</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from Missahohe and Kete-Kratchi, and from South 
<collectingCountry box="[978,1031,710,734]" name="Togo" pageId="12" pageNumber="337">Togo</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="STERNFELD L." box="[1039,1207,710,734]" pageId="12" pageNumber="337" pagination="207 - 236" refId="ref29004" refString="STERNFELD L. 1908 b. - Die Schlangenfauna Togos. Mittheilungen Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 4: 207 - 236." type="journal article" year="1908">Sternfeld (1908b</bibRefCitation>
