<paragraph blockId="12.[675,1211,892,1101]" pageId="12" pageNumber="337">
CONSERVATION STATUS. — According to reports of the CITES Division of the DFC 
<collectingCountry box="[958,1010,918,942]" name="Togo" pageId="12" pageNumber="337">Togo</collectingCountry>
, 37 living specimens were exported from 
<collectingCountry box="[876,926,944,968]" name="Togo" pageId="12" pageNumber="337">Togo</collectingCountry>
between 2003 and 2005. In 
<date box="[678,805,971,995]" pageId="12" pageNumber="337" value="2007-03">March 2007</date>
, we observed 
<specimenCount box="[948,1083,971,995]" pageId="12" pageNumber="337" type="generic">52 specimens</specimenCount>
in the Mare snake farm, intended to be forwarded to a South African laboratory according to the manager of this farm. These specimens were collected in the vicinity of Tsevie in ER V.
</paragraph>
